1. Connected and wanted to test connection so when i did provider i also used
data "aws_caller_identity" "current" {} 
then i removed once i established my aws account connection was succesful.

2. Create a senior level tree. 
terraform-multi-tier-webapp/
├── README.md
├── main.tf
├── variables.tf
├── outputs.tf
├── provider.tf
├── terraform.tfvars
├── backend.tf           # Remote state configuration
├── modules/
│   ├── networking/
│   │   ├── main.tf
│   │   ├── variables.tf
│   │   ├── outputs.tf
│   │   └── security.tf   # Optional: Network ACLs, security groups
│   ├── compute/
│   │   ├── main.tf
│   │   ├── variables.tf
│   │   ├── outputs.tf
│   │   └── userdata.sh   # Optional: EC2 startup script
│   ├── database/
│   │   ├── main.tf
│   │   ├── variables.tf
│   │   ├── outputs.tf
│   │   └── security.tf   # Optional: DB-specific SGs
│   └── storage/
│       ├── main.tf
│       ├── variables.tf
│       └── outputs.tf
├── environments/
│   ├── dev/
│   │   ├── main.tf      # Calls modules with dev-specific vars
│   │   └── terraform.tfvars
│   └── prod/
│       ├── main.tf      # Calls modules with prod-specific vars
│       └── terraform.tfvars
├── scripts/
│   └── init.sh          # Optional: bootstrap script
└── .gitignore
